OL,3,C'Absolute hell': Villagers on HS2 line
OL,4,Csay they're still living a nightmare
OL,6,FHowever, some in the village have
OL,7,Fbenefited from the arrival of HS2.
OL,9,FWater Orton & District Tennis Club is
OL,10,Fone a number of community venues to
OL,11,Fhave received a grant from HS2,
OL,12,Fallowing it to pay for much-needed
OL,13,Fimprovements.
OL,15,FIt's Chairman, Paul Messenger said:
OL,16,F"HS2 funded our floodlights and until
OL,17,Fthey did that we were a club that
OL,18,Fplayed six months a year and now we
OL,19,Fcan play all year."
